Brent Harold Liles (September 7, 1963 – January 18, 2007) was as American musician who was the bassist for Social Distortion from 1981–1984 and later was the bassist for Agent Orange from 1988 – 1992.
Liles was born on September 7, 1963, and was an only child.
His father died in a plane crash when Brent was 8 years old.
He continued to live with his mother and was a standout tennis player at Troy High School in Fullerton, California, and salutatorian of his high school graduating class in 1981.
He appeared on Social Distortion's 1983 classic debut Mommy's Little Monster before leaving the band on New Year's Day 1984, with the band's drummer Derek O'Brien.
